        <description>Interacts with the user to gather the payment plan details. Creates a payment schedule according to the user’s inputs, and sends an email to the user with the payment extension details.</description>
        <developerName>PaymentExtensionRequestsASA_16jWs000000Z1m1</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Before you respond to the user, get the details for the collection plan record to learn the context of the user’s query or request. If user has already selected or provided a collection Plan name of format CP-***** use this, else ask the user to provide one.</description>
            <developerName>getcollectionplaninfo</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>get-collection-plan-info</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Get the most recent payment schedule record associated with the collection plan Name. 
 Check if the payment schedule was created within the last 24 hours. If it was, ask the user  if they still want to create another payment schedule for the most recent payment commitment details. 
 Always present the values in a numbered list and ask the user to enter the number for the payment schedule record creation option. 
 Yes 
 No 
 If user says yes, set shouldIgnoreRecentPaymentExtnRequest to True and trigger the Request Payment Extension Action. 
 If the user says no, set shouldIgnoreRecentPaymentExtnRequest to False and trigger the Request Payment Extension Action.</description>
            <developerName>handlerecentlycreatedpaymentschedule</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>handle-recently-created-payment-schedule</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>The Name of collectionPlan record always starts with &quot;CP&quot;, always verify it before assigning it to the collectionPlanName variable of RequestPaymentExtensionASA action.</description>
            <developerName>checkname</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>check-name</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Use RequestPaymentExtensionASA action to create payment schedule and payment schedule item records according to payment extension commitment. 
 Talk in third person as a collection specialist. Before calling the action.
 Before calling the action, ask the customer about full payment or partial payment. Always present the values in a numbered list and ask the customer to enter the number for the payment option. 
 Full Payment 
 Partial Payment 
 If a user enters an invalid value, ask the user to select a valid value from the list.
 If the user selects Partial Payment, ask the user to enter the payment amount. 
 Ask the user how many installments they would like to use to pay, regardless of whether they chose full payment or partial payment. 
 After the user has entered the number of installments, ask the user to enter a payment processing date and payment amount for each installment sequentially. 
 Always present the installment number and the corresponding values using an unordered list and ask the user to enter the details. 
 Installment 1 
 Payment Amount 
 Payment Processing Date 
 The user can choose to enter all the details at once or one at a time. 
 Use the payment amount and payment processing date for all the installments to create Installments as per the Apex file.</description>
            <developerName>takeinputs</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>take-inputs</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user enters the payment amount, check if they also enter a currency symbol or currency ISOCode. If they don&apos;t, use the CurrencyISOCode field of the CollectionPlan. If they do, check if it same as the CurrencyISOCode field of CollectionPlan. If it is different, convert it to the supported currency and ask user for confirmation. 
 Do not create the payment extension or payment schedules if the user wants to create it in a different currency than the CurrencyISOCode of CollectionPlan. Politely decline if they are not willing to convert.</description>
            <developerName>currencyconversion</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>currency-conversion</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Only on successful execution of action at the end, Display message &quot;We have recorded your inputs regarding your commitment to make the payment on the specified dates. We will review and if required someone from team will reach out.&quot; Along with this display the flow successful message. 
 Don&apos;t show or display any link after the success.</description>
            <developerName>successmessage</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>success-message</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
